President Biden has declared a major disaster in Kentucky due to severe storms, winds, tornadoes, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from December 31, 2021, to January 2, 2022. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available to local governments, certain nonprofit organizations, and private entities for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures will also be supported throughout the Commonwealth. John Brogan has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.